{"title_page": "Dostana (1980 film)", "text_new": "{{For|the 2008 film|Dostana (2008 film)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Dostana\n| image          = Dostana 1980.JPG\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[Raj Khosla]]\n| producer       = [[Yash Johar]]\n| writer         = [[Salim-Javed]]\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = [[Amitabh Bachchan]]<br>[[Shatrughan Sinha]]<br>[[Zeenat Aman]]<br>[[Prem Chopra]]<br>[[Amrish Puri]]<br>[[Helen (actress)|Helen]]<br>[[Pran (actor)|Pran]]\n| music          = [[Laxmikant-Pyarelal]]\n| cinematography = [[Nariman A. Irani]]\n| editing        = Waman Bhonsle\n| studio         = \n| distributor    = [[Dharma Productions]] <br>[[Yash Raj Films]]\n| released       = {{film date|df=y|1980|10|8}}\n| runtime        = 153 mins\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Dostana''''' (\"Friendship\") is a [[1980]] Indian [[action film|action]]-[[drama film]], written by [[Salim-Javed]], produced by [[Yash Johar]], and directed by [[Raj Khosla]]. The film stars [[Amitabh Bachchan]], [[Shatrughan Sinha]], [[Zeenat Aman]], [[Prem Chopra]], [[Amrish Puri]], [[Helen (actress)|Helen]], [[Pran (actor)|Pran]] and [[Paintal]]. The film was a huge hit <ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=4407 |title= The Biggest Diwali BLOCKBUSTERS Of All Time |publisher= boxofficeindia.com |date=7 November 2018 |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref> and the fourth highest-grosser of 1980, behind ''[[Qurbani]]'', ''[[Asha]]'' and ''[[Ram Balram]]''. ''Dostana'' was one of the last successful films directed by [[Raj Khosla]]. The film was remade in Tamil as ''[[Sattam]]'', with [[Kamal Haasan]].\n\n==Plot==\nVijay ([[Amitabh Bachchan]]) and Ravi ([[Shatrughan Sinha]]) are best friends who do not question each other about their careers. Vijay is a police officer and Ravi is a lawyer. While Vijay catches criminals, Ravi bails those criminals out and is employed by Daaga ([[Prem Chopra]]). One day both Vijay and Ravi meet Sheetal ([[Zeenat Aman]]) at different places and times, and both fall in love with her. While Vijay's love is more vocal and is reciprocated by Sheetal, Ravi has one-sided crush on Sheetal.\n\nRavi admits his love for Sheetal to Vijay who is devastated but decides to sacrifice his love for Ravi's sake. However, there is a misunderstanding when Daaga decides to stir up Vijay and Ravi's friendship by showing Ravi a photo of Vijay and Sheetal. Vijay and Ravi become rivals for the first time. The rest of the movie looks at the conflict between Vijay and Daaga. After the misunderstanding, Ravi is on Daaga's side but later learns the truth and atones for his deeds.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Amitabh Bachchan]] as Vijay Varma\n*[[Shatrughan Sinha]] as Ravi Kapoor\n*[[Zeenat Aman]] as Sheetal Sahni\n*[[Prem Chopra]] as Daaga\n*[[Amrish Puri]] as Balwant Singh\n*[[Helen (actress)|Helen]] as Sylvia\n*[[Pran (actor)|Pran]] as Tony\n*[[Gajanan Jagirdar]] as High School Principal\n*[[Sajjan (actor)|Sajjan]] as Ramniklal Tiwari\n*[[Iftekhar]] as Prosecuting Lawyer\n*[[K.N. Singh]] as Judge\n*[[Paintal]] as Eve-teaser (Guest Appearance) \n*[[Jagdish Raj]] as Driver (Daaga's Man)\n*[[Sudhir]] as Inspector Shinde\n*[[Mac Mohan]] as Daaga's Man\n*[[Sharat Saxena]] as Photographer (Daaga's Man)\n*[[Ruby Mayer]] as Nun\n*[[Yunus Parvez]] as Gold Smuggler\n*[[Goga Kapoor]] as Baldev Singh\n*[[Vikas Anand]] as Dr. Karamchandani\n*[[Mohan Sherry]] as Daaga's Man\n\n\nIn the film where [[Amitabh Bachchan]] beats [[Sajjan (actor)|Sajjan]] in the prison and after that, [[Sajjan (actor)|Sajjan]] was killed by another prisoner, the same scene was copied by [[Raj Khosla]] from his own directed film [[C.I.D. (1956 film)|CID]], where the same circumstances were faced by [[Dev Anand]]. [[Dostana's]] Producer was [[Yash Johar]] and later his son [[Karan Johar]] also producer made a movie same name [[Dostana (2008 film)|Dostana]] starring [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[John Abraham]] and [[Priyanka Chopra]].\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\nThe music for ''Dostana'' was composed by the duo [[Laxmikant-Pyarelal]] and the lyrics were written by [[Anand Bakshi]]. \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Song\n!Singer\n|-\n|\"Salaamat Rahe Dostana Hamara\" - (Part 1)\n|[[Mohammad Rafi]], [[Kishore Kumar]]\n|-\n|\"Salaamat Rahe Dostana Hamara\" - (Part 2)\n|[[Mohammad Rafi]], [[Kishore Kumar]]\n|-\n|\"Mere Dost Kissa Yeh Kya Ho Gaya\"\n|[[Mohammad Rafi]]\n|-\n|\"Bahut Khoobsurat Jawaan Ek Ladki\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]]\n|-\n|\"Dillagi Ne Di Hawaa\"\n|[[Kishore Kumar]], [[Asha Bhosle]]\n|-\n|\"Kitna Aasan Hai Kehna Bhool Jaao\"\n|[[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Nominations==\n*[[Filmfare]] Nomination for Best Actor--[[Amitabh Bachchan]]\n*[[Filmfare]] Nomination for Best Actor--[[Shatrughan Sinha]]\n*[[Filmfare]] Nomination for Best Lyricist--[[Anand Bakshi]] for the song \"Salamat Rahe\"\n*[[Filmfare]] Nomination for Best Male Playback Singer--[[Mohd. Rafi]] for the song \"Mere Dost Kissa\"[http://deep750.googlepages.com/FilmfareAwards.pdf]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0080653|Dostana}}\n\n{{Salim-Javed}}\n{{Dharma Productions}}\n\n[[Category:1980 films]]\n[[Category:1980s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:1980s action drama films]]\n[[Category:1980s buddy films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Raj Khosla]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Laxmikant\u2013Pyarelal]]\n[[Category:Hindi films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian action drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian buddy films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Salim-Javed]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language films]]\n[[Category:Urdu films remade in other languages]]\n\n\n{{1980s-Hindi-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|the 2008 film|Dostana (2008 film)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Dostana\n| image          = Dostana 1980.JPG\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[Raj Khosla]]\n| producer       = [[Yash Johar]]\n| writer         = [[Salim-Javed]]\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = [[Amitabh Bachchan]]<br>[[Shatrughan Sinha]]<br>[[Zeenat Aman]]<br>[[Prem Chopra]]<br>[[Amrish Puri]]<br>[[Helen]]<br>[[Pran]]\n| music          = [[Laxmikant-Pyarelal]]\n| cinematography = [[Nariman A. Irani]]\n| editing        = Waman Bhonsle\n| studio         = \n| distributor    = [[Dharma Productions]] <br>[[Yash Raj Films]]\n| released       = {{film date|df=y|1980|10|8}}\n| runtime        = 153 mins\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Dostana''''' (\"Friendship\") is a [[1980]] Indian [[action]]-[[drama film]], written by [[Salim-Javed]], produced by [[Yash Johar]], and directed by [[Raj Khosla]]. The film stars [[Amitabh Bachchan]], [[Shatrughan Sinha]], [[Zeenat Aman]], [[Prem Chopra]], [[Amrish Puri]], [[Helen]], [[Pran]] and [[Paintal]]. The film was a huge hit <ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=4407 |title= The Biggest Diwali BLOCKBUSTERS Of All Time |publisher= boxofficeindia.com |date=7 November 2018 |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref> and the fourth highest-grosser of 1980, behind ''[[Qurbani]]'', ''[[Asha]]'' and ''[[Ram Balram]]''. ''[[Dostana]]'' was one of the last successful films directed by [[Raj Khosla]]. The film was remade in Tamil as ''[[Sattam]]'', with [[Kamal Haasan]].\n\n==Plot==\nVijay ([[Amitabh Bachchan]]) and Ravi ([[Shatrughan Sinha]]) are best friends who do not question each other about their careers. Vijay is a police officer and Ravi is a lawyer. While Vijay catches criminals, Ravi bails those criminals out and is employed by Daaga ([[Prem Chopra]]). One day both Vijay and Ravi meet Sheetal ([[Zeenat Aman]]) at different places and times, and both fall in love with her. While Vijay's love is more vocal and is reciprocated by Sheetal, Ravi has one-sided crush on Sheetal.\n\nRavi admits his love for Sheetal to Vijay who is devastated but decides to sacrifice his love for Ravi's sake. However, there is a misunderstanding when Daaga decides to stir up Vijay and Ravi's friendship by showing Ravi a photo of Vijay and Sheetal. Vijay and Ravi become rivals for the first time. The rest of the movie looks at the conflict between Vijay and Daaga. After the misunderstanding, Ravi is on Daaga's side but later learns the truth and atones for his deeds.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Amitabh Bachchan]] as Vijay Varma\n*[[Shatrughan Sinha]] as Ravi Kapoor\n*[[Zeenat Aman]] as Sheetal Sahni\n*[[Prem Chopra]] as Daaga\n*[[Amrish Puri]] as Balwant Singh\n*[[Helen]] as Sylvia\n*[[Pran]] as Tony\n*[[Gajanan Jagirdar]] as High School Principal\n*[[Sajjan]] as Ramniklal Tiwari\n*[[Iftekhar]] as Prosecuting Lawyer\n*[[K.N. Singh]] as Judge\n*[[Paintal]] as Eve-teaser (Guest Appearance) \n*[[Jagdish Raj]] as Driver (Daaga's Man)\n*[[Sudhir]] as Inspector Shinde\n*[[Mac Mohan]] as Daaga's Man\n*[[Sharat Saxena]] as Photographer (Daaga's Man)\n*[[Ruby Mayer]] as Nun\n*[[Yunus Parvez]] as Gold Smuggler\n*[[Goga Kapoor]] as Baldev Singh\n*[[Vikas Anand]] as Dr. Karamchandani\n*[[Mohan Sherry]] as Daaga's Man\n\n\nIn the film where [[Amitabh Bachchan]] beats [[Sajjan]] in the prison and after that, [[Sajjan]] was killed by another prisoner, the same scene was copied by [[Raj Khosla]] from his own directed film [[CID]], where the same circumstances were faced by [[Dev Anand]]. [[Dostana's]] Producer was [[Yash Johar]] and later his son [[Karan Johar]] also producer made a movie same name [[Dostana]] starring [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[John Abraham]] and [[Priyanka Chopra]].\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\nThe music for ''[[Dostana]]'' was composed by the duo [[Laxmikant-Pyarelal]] and the lyrics were written by [[Anand Bakshi]]. \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n